Sethuraman vs Bharathakoti Harsha 
Indian Qualifier, rd 1.5, May-7 (2021)
Ruy Lopez, Moeller defence (C78)

PGN here https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/indian-qualifier-2021/1/6/5

The Indian Qualifier is a 16-player knockout tournament taking place from 7-10 May 2021 on chess24. The format is the same as for the Meltwater Champions Chess Tour except that there is only one set of matches instead of two. The top 2 qualify for a Tour event.

The matches consist of four Rapid games (15+10). If tied, a 2-game blitz mini-match (5+3) is played and if still tied, an Armageddon game (5 vs 4 with draw odds for Black) decides the winner of the match.
